The lawmaker representing Mushin Federal constituency in the House of Representatives, Adeyemi Alli, has empowered about 1,000 constituents with vocational equipment. At the ‘Super Empowerment’ in Olorunsogo in Mushin, Alli described empowerment programmes ‘as a potent channel to eradicate poverty, social exclusions, unemployment, high vulnerability to environmental risks and socio-economic challenges’. The lawmaker explained that the way to support the socio-economic policies of both state and local government, was through provision of empowerment equipment to facilitate wealth creation, self-employment and a peaceful and prosperous society. He admonished the beneficiaries to make judicious use of the items, warning them not to sell them for quick cash.   2023: ‘Zoning good, but competence better’     Council to go after debtors     Media firm unveils Lagos Show Podcast   He said a monitoring team had been set up to ensure this. - Advertisement - All Progressives Congress (APC) chieftain Senator Ganiu Solomon hailed Alli for impacting the lives of his constituents, and implored the beneficiaries to use the items well. He appealed to those who yet to benefit to be patient. The empowerment package include tricycles, sewing machines, grinding machines, freezers, hair dryers, laptops, hand dryers, among others.